47
00:02:48.350 --> 00:02:51.031
So there's a lot, in your design system,

48
00:02:51.031 --> 00:02:54.909
can be bigger than just a load
of components in figma and code.

49
00:02:54.909 --> 00:03:00.461
But that can come later, as I was saying
in the course that I ran previously.

50
00:03:00.461 --> 00:03:02.080
Something is better than nothing.

51
00:03:02.080 --> 00:03:04.068
Don't despise those small beginnings.

52
00:03:04.068 --> 00:03:06.995
Start with the basics and
build up from there.

53
00:03:06.995 --> 00:03:10.720
So just to wrap that talk
about design systems up,

54
00:03:10.720 --> 00:03:14.278
a design system is an invaluable tool,
right?

55
00:03:14.278 --> 00:03:16.838
If it's planned carefully, right?

56
00:03:16.838 --> 00:03:21.058
Or it can be an enormous waste of money
and time, so be careful about that.

57
00:03:21.058 --> 00:03:25.657
When creating a design system, start with
your styles, move on to your elements, and

58
00:03:25.657 --> 00:03:27.548
finally work on those components.

59
00:03:27.548 --> 00:03:34.006
But remember that design system is gonna
need a carefully considered rollout.

60
00:03:34.006 --> 00:03:36.558
And that it's much more than
a set of UI elements, and

61
00:03:36.558 --> 00:03:38.332
you can build upon that long-term.

